pageContext.claim: “He's a very highly respected, conservative pundit. He's a big Trump fan. That was a retweet. That wasn't from me; that was from him. But he's a man who has half a million followers. A lot of followers. And he's respected.”
pageContext.analysis: Terrence K. Williams is a comedian who tweeted a conspiracy theory suggesting Bill Clinton had Jeffrey Epstein murdered. (Epstein committed suicide, officials determined.) Trump retweeted that. Just because someone has 500,000 Twitter does not mean that they are "respected."
